% --------------- Abstract page -----------------------
\begin{center}
{\Large{\bf{ABSTRACT}}}
\end{center}


The main aim of the project is to study Fourier transform on $L^1(\mathbb{R}^n)$ and extend the definition to $L^p(\mathbb{R}^n), ~1<p\leq2$ using two
approaches, by using density argument and by using Hermite polynomials. We define Fourier transform on $L^1(\mathbb{R}^n)$ and discuss some properties of Fourier transform, extend the definition to $L^p(\mathbb{R}^n), ~1<p\leq2$ and finally prove Hardy's theorem on $\mathbb{R}^n$.

